Also, just on a personal note, a toddler 16-18 months old that I met in Costa Rica saw a picture of Jesus that I had and immediately grabbed it away from me, gave it dozen kisses and said over and over JeeJee JeeJee.  This family lived in a one room shack, and did not attend any church.  The child just 'recognized' Him.  I dont buy that children are natural born atheists.<br>
<br>
You also said there are no miracles that occur today and that God isnt talking to anyone? - Sorry, I have personally had miracles in my life and the life of my family.  One such example was my dh met a woman in CA while on his mission.  This woman had had a brain aneurysm and had the mental capabilty of a child.  He and the other missionary that were with him gave her a blessing and she was Miraculously cured.  Her brain function returned to normal.  Faith alone isnt going to rebuild brain pathways - I know enough about medicine to know that brain cells just dont repair themselves instantaneously. Someone else (God) had a hand in it.<br>
