<br>
I respect people like Candy and Shirene who will go toe-to-toe 9 rounds of courteous debate and argument, each testing my reason and logic, but not my patience.  I have immense respect for many of the caring and loving parents who do what they feel is best for their children.  I respect and admire the people, I do not respect or admire the theology that has them in its grasp.  Those people are the musicians who play piano because the music is beautiful, religion is the thug who will break their legs if they don’t play.  Close your eyes to millennia of rape, oppression, destruction and murder, I prefer to work to keep it from happening again. The saddest part is that these wonderful people, these beautiful musicians, feel they need this ugly thug to be the wonderful beings they are.  They cannot imagine life without him.<br>
<br>
Add ‘Atlas Shrugged’ by Ayn Rand to your reading list.<br>
